pip install %package_name%
pip list (list all the packages with versions)
pip list -o / --outdated (lists outdated packages)
pip freeze : output installed packages in requirements format

Command to upgrade outdated packages all at once:
pip3 freeze | grep -v '^\-e' | cut -d = -f 1 | xargs -n1 pip3 install -U

Install packages from a file in requirements format:
pip install -r %filename%

